products.title: The Warley Fall (Two Gallon) - Exclusive
products.body_html: When it’s time to refresh your plant care routine, choose Haws’ Warley Fall. A favorite among expert gardeners, this watering can effortlessly reaches deep into flowerbeds with its extra-long spout, while the downspout is perfect for hanging baskets and pots. It includes a non-drip brass rose that delivers a delicate rainfall spray, and carries an impressive two gallons (or 9l), so it’ll keep watering when most other cans have stopped. Crafted from galvanized and powder-coated steel for lasting durability, this limited edition can comes in a rich, nature-inspired colorway exclusive to Goodee. Plus, it's beautifully presented in a gift-ready Haws box.

products.title: Sentei Garden Scissors
products.body_html: Need scissors that can handle both delicate flowers and woodier stems? Niwaki’s Sentei Garden Scissors are for you. Expertly crafted from high-quality carbon steel in Japan, they provide sharp, precise cuts (which is healthier for your plants), and will last for decades with proper maintenance. The round handles provide a comfortable grip, perfect for delicate work and substantial tasks alike, and they’re ideal for smaller hands. For best results, use the tips for careful work and make bigger cuts further down the blades.

products.title: Weeding Fork
products.body_html: Looking for a weeding fork that's gentle on roots and tough on weeds? Meet the Sneeboer Weeding Fork. With robust stainless steel tines and comfortable FSC-certified hardwood handles, it effortlessly lifts weeds (or removes plants from pots or soil) without harming the roots. The clever design ensures that the tool is not only sturdy but also balanced and ergonomical to use. Hand-forged in the Netherlands, this weeding fork embodies Sneeboer's legacy of handcrafted excellence, making it an indispensable part of your gardening toolkit for years to come.

products.title: Bicycle Basket (Large)
products.body_html: In search of a robust front basket that adds flair to your bike rides? Beautifully handwoven in Ghana from elephant grass, Baba Tree's fair-trade bicycle basket is ideal for daily errands and picnics in the parks. Two adjustable leather straps with brass buckles tightly secure your basket to the handlebars for a smooth ride, with exceptional craftsmanship ensuring long-lasting quality.

products.title: Pakurigo Basket
products.body_html:
Boasting the intricate patterns, shapes and expert weaving techniques of Baba Tree's Ghanaian artisans, the Pakurigo basket features a wave-like silhouette that few weavers are able to master.

Crafted from flexible yet strong elephant grass, the Pakurigo's wide diameter allows for easy storage in your home, from extra blankets near the sofa, to children's toys, or cold-weather accessories tucked conveniently near the entryway. Each basket features a singular design created by its weaver, ranging in colors and patterns from simple neutrals to bright, complex creations.

products.title: Wooden Box Set of 6 with Incense Mat and Dish
products.body_html: Elevate your daily rituals or delight a dear friend with exquisite HA KO leaf-shaped incense. Delicately crafted from Japanese washi paper and infused with natural essential oils, each one of these dreamy incense leaves offers a distinct scent to evoke different moods: No.1 Spicy Jasmine, No.3 Elegance Citrus, No.5 Smoky Cinnamon, No.6 White Floral, No.7 Green Grass, and No.8 True Aqua. If you can’t bear to burn these beauties, they’ll double as potpourri. The set comes with an unglazed plate and non-flammable felt pad thoughtfully packaged in a wooden box — details that make this gift all the more delightful.

products.title: Large Tumbler, set of 2
products.body_html:
Need beautiful glassware that’s perfect whether you’re sipping water or something a little stronger? This exquisite Xaquixe set comprising two large tumbler glasses will bring joy to any occasion with its fluid shape, playful pattern, and sustainable credentials. Hand-crafted in Oaxaca, Mexico using locally-sourced recycled glass and alternative energy, each tumbler is remarkably sturdy and durable enough to withstand the rigors of daily use. A celebration of the artisan collective’s innovative spirit and powerful vision for change.

Every Xaquixe glass is blown by hand, meaning that no two are alike.

products.title: Smiley Goat Planter
products.body_html:
Not into minimalist plant pots? Then this quirky goat planter by Malaika is the perfect pick for your flowers and leafy friends. Expertly hand-crafted in the oasis village of Tunis in Fayoum by master potter Mohamed Mahmoud, this ceramic piece beautifully showcases the boldness and creativity of contemporary Egyptian craftsmanship, while bringing a touch of whimsy to your decor. Place it on your windowsill or on your porch and wait for your guests’ reaction.

Malaika’s Fayoum Pottery is entirely handcrafted, so you may find slight imperfections, color variations, and minor sizing differences.

products.title: Hedgehog Table Brush
products.body_html: There’s nothing like a Hedgehog Table Brush to make cleaning up more fun. Expertly hand-crafted in Germany from oil-treated, beechwood and horsehair, this adorable handheld duster by Redecker is the perfect eco-friendly alternative to paper towels or disposable wipes to keep your surfaces spotless. It’s very effective too, as the dense yet soft bristles attract the tiniest particles and gently sweep them away. (It works just as nicely to clean up the narrow gaps in computer keyboards.) Bonus: Toddlers will love learning to tidy up with it.

products.title: Incense Gift Set of 5 with Incense Mat
products.body_html: Treat yourself or surprise someone special with this delightful gift – a thoughtful gesture anyone will appreciate. This elegant box set includes five unique HA KO incense leaves, exquisitely crafted from washi paper and infused with natural essential oils on Awaji Island, the birthplace of Japanese incense. Each delicately fragranced paper leaf offers a distinct scent to evoke different moods: No.1 Spicy Jasmine, No.2 Agar Wood, No.3 Elegance Citrus, No.4 Sandalwood, and No.5 Smoky Cinnamon. A testament to tradition and quality, these enchanting incense leaves can be enjoyed as potpourri or used as incense to enhance your space and daily rituals.

products.title: Koma Candle Stand
products.body_html:
Looking for a fitting home for your beloved Takazawa Candles? The Koma is the answer. Specifically designed to hold your Japanese candles, this cast iron candle stand ensures they shine in all their glory with its minimalist aesthetic. Meticulously crafted by an iron artisan in Japan using rust-resistant and long-lasting Nambu ironware, its elegant and stable form seamlessly harmonizes with diverse decor styles, making it the ideal addition to any space

The Small stand fits the Tohaku Small Candle by Takazawa Candle. The Medium stand fits the Nanao Medium and TOHAKU Medium Candles by Takazawa Candle.

Goodee-Takazawa-Koma Candle Stand - Color - Black - Size - Medium

products.title: Higurashi GR Secateurs
products.body_html:
Whether you're pruning trees and houseplants or cutting woody stems for your flower arrangements, Niwaki's Higurashi Secateurs will make any task effortless with their strong, sharp blades. Handcrafted with the finest drop-forged carbon steel in an old family-run Japanese factory, these pruners are designed with attention to detail, from their slightly textured handles to the chunky catch. Delivering long-lasting quality and a refined cutting action, this trusty tool is perfect for all-day use and will serve you for years.

Although Japanese carbon steel is durable, it can chip if mishandled, so use with care.

products.title: Lump Vase
products.body_html: In need of a unique, responsibly-designed vase to spruce up your space? Or perhaps an eye-catching centerpiece that's beautiful even without blooms? You'll love ferm LIVING's Lump Vase. Adorned with hand-placed, uneven glass dots, this vase brings a unique charm to any space. Each piece is mouth-blown and handcrafted from recycled glass, making it a one-of-a-kind creation. The Lump Vase doesn't just hold your favorite blooms — it stands as a testament to sustainable design and exceptional craftsmanship.

products.title: The Rowley Ripple (Two Pint)
products.body_html:
Haws is synonymous with top-quality watering cans, and the Rowley Ripple 2 Pint is a shining example of the brand’s fine craftsmanship tradition. With its gracefully curved spout, this elegant metal can offers unmatched balance and precision, while the removable oval non-drip brass rose delivers the most perfect spray for delicate seedlings, small plants, and pots. Crafted to last, it will keep your garden or greenhouse looking beautiful for years to come. (Plus, it comes in an attractive, gift-ready Haws box.) Each can take more than 200 steps to complete, part of a tradition of quality that dates back to 1886.

Copper cans might have minor imperfections upon arrival, which can be rectified by following the instructions provided below.

This splendid plant mister delivers a fine spray to your tropical houseplants and brings a touch of gleaming elegance to your space. Ideal for tending to your terrariums, orchids and succulents, it gently tops up their humidity while keeping their leaves dust-free. A beautiful object, it's available in a choice of handsome metallic finishes, making the perfect present for any design-savvy plant lover.

products.title: Hoff Planter Ø14
products.body_html:
Searching for a design-forward terracotta pot for your succulents or cacti (or any plant that prefers dry soil)? The Hoff Planter by Bergs Potter would be perfect for showing them off with its simple and refreshing silhouette. Designed by Danish graphical designer Anne Hoff and crafted from the finest Italian clay in a small Tuscan village, this long-lasting pot will look beautiful no matter where you place it — on your windowsill, desktop, or outside on the balcony — and it will look even better with age. Pair with a glazed Hoff Saucer for a playful touch that perfectly reflects your style.

This pot is frost resistant and has a drainage hole to keep your plant healthy. Hoff saucers are sold separately.

products.title: Copenhagen Pot Ø18
products.body_html:
What could be more fitting than a pot with royal roots to elevate your houseplant collection? Inspired by a pot first manufactured at the royal castle in Denmark in 1860, the Copenhagen by Bergs Potter (also called the Castle Pot) makes a distinguished addition to your plant sanctuary. Hand-crafted in a small Tuscan village from the finest Italian clay and glazed with care, this pot will last for decades indoors as well as outdoors, becoming even more beautiful with age.

This pot is frost resistant and has a drainage hole to keep your plant healthy.

products.title: Hoff Saucer Ø18
products.body_html: You've found the perfect plant pot, and you’re now looking for a saucer to match (and catch excess water). Enter the Hoff Saucer by Bergs Potter. Designed by Danish graphical designer Anne Hoff, this sleek piece is hand-crafted at a small family-owned workshop in Tuscany using the finest Italian clay, then hand-dipped with glaze for a glossy finish. The perfect companion to the Hoff Planter in raw terracotta — with four luscious colors to choose from — this saucer can be used both indoors and outdoors.

products.title: Kenzan
products.body_html:
Whether you're a seasoned floral designer or just starting out, a traditional Japanese Kenzan (or flower frog) will take your flower arranging skills to the next level. This tried-and-true florist tool, traditionally used in the ancient art of ikebana, provides a reliable base for keeping stems in place and a sustainable alternative to floral foam. Niwaki's round version is expertly crafted in Japan with strong brass pins that can hold woody and green stalks alike while naturally opening the stems for better water absorption, ensuring your blooms last longer.

Niwaki’s products are crafted to last for years. With proper care, the Japanese carbon steel will stay sharp and usable, and your Niwaki products can be passed onto future generations.

products.title: Snake Cushion
products.body_html: Whether you have a set of chairs or bench-style seating that needs a comfort boost, the Snake Cushion from Fogo Island Workshops is just the ticket. Created collaboratively by local artisans for the Fogo Island Inn, this exquisite piece faithfully revives a traditional design by Fogo Islander Elizabeth Ford. With remarkable ingenuity, each cushion is meticulously hand-crafted from the tiniest scraps of wool yarn. This reversible piece offers both a joyful splash of color and comfort, and each one is distinctly unique.

products.title: Lidded Bird Box
products.body_html:
The perfect spot to store your tiny treasures, from jewelry to coins or even keys, this decorative Bird Box by Tinja adds substance and soul to any space. Molded by hand by the women artisans of Sejnane using locally harvested clay and techniques passed down through generations, its design evokes the shores of Lake Ichkeul, a nature reserve listed as a UNESCO World Heritage site and a wintering place for many bird species. The perfect addition to a mantel, bookshelf, or vanity.

Due to the handmade nature of this item, no two pieces are exactly alike.

Please note that Sejnane pottery is not waterproof. If you want to use this pot as a vase, be sure to place another container for water inside.

products.title: Kapok Mattress Bedroll
products.body_html:
Lightweight, slim and ultra-comfortable, this mattress provides a soft overlay that can be easily layered for rest and relaxation. Its hand-spun cotton exterior is complemented by an interior made of 100% kapok, a natural and hypoallergenic fiber that is picked, shelled and filled by hand. Available in a variety of rich, hand-dyed colors, including the brand's signature indigo, Tensira pairs careful craftsmanship with customizable comfort. Recline across several for a more plush feel or opt to use one as a cozy covering as you rest.

Please note that as each mattress is handmade, dimensions may vary slightly.

products.title: Kapok Mattress Rectangular
products.body_html:
If you’re creating a cozy corner for curling up with a good book or simply daydreaming away, this beautifully crafted mattress bedroll by Tensira is the perfect place to start. Lightweight, slim, and ultra-comfortable, it provides a soft overlay that can be easily layered for rest and relaxation. Its hand-spun cotton exterior showcases West Africa’s exquisite craftsmanship, as well as the brand's signature hand-dyed indigo, while the interior is entirely filled with kapok — a soft and silky natural fiber that is picked and shelled by hand. Fold your mattress up to support your sitting posture or stack several up on the floor for a plush lounge set up.

Please note that as each mattress is handmade, dimensions may vary slightly.

products.title: Laundry Basket
products.body_html:
If you have to — or want to — leave your laundry hamper out in the open, the Baba Tree laundry basket is the one for you. Crafted by hand in Ghana with sturdy palm leaves, this tastefully woven design is spacious enough to hold an entire week's worth of clothes and stylish enough for your space. (Plus, it comes with a lid to conceal unsightly piles.) It’s so elegant, in fact, that it can be used in any room as extra storage for pillows, toys, shoes, and more.

Every Baba Tree piece is crafted under ethical working conditions and provides a meaningful income for its maker.

products.title: All Bright Set
products.body_html:
Setting up a play/learn corner in a kids’ room or living room? This pint-sized ecoBirdy set is sure to please. Consisting of a table with two chairs in different colorways, it offers the ideal spot for little ones to paint, read, build things, and even enjoy their meals from 18 months up to 7 years old. Crafted from ecothylene — an exclusive material made of recycled plastic toys — the set is easy to carry around and wipe clean, making it well-suited for indoor and outdoor use.

Includes:
1 Luisa Table (Party)
2 Charlie Chairs (Off-white)

Please note that this furniture is suitable for kids from the ages of 18 months up to 7 years old to sit on. We do not recommend the chair to be used by adults.

Presented in a beautiful box, it makes a fine gift.
